{
  "stem": "18281.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so the wrath of the Austrian population was really against those foreigners that, besides being dressed funny, spoke funny.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they spoke some Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the Yiddish was certainly not close to the Viennese accent.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the-- you asked me about the Austrian Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, they kind of look down at those strangers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And, and, and of course the, the Jewish Committee helped.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They gave them some money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they had some field kitchens.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I remember that those people were standing in line in order to get some soup.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we, we kind of looked down at them like if they were some kind of second rate citizens.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were not citizens at all.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did not associate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did not go to school with them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember that in my class, we had a few Jews, I believe six or seven.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the rest where Austrians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They certainly did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They lived in the second district of Vienna, which had the nickname of Mazzesinsel, which means Matzo's Island.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's where they lived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they have their own synagogues and--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They have their own synagogues, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, stores or stands at the markets.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were peddling goods.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one of the, of those people that became famous in Canada is the Reichmann family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They come from Hungary near the Austrian border.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were selling Hungarian chickens in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And because in those days a religious Jew could not enter a bank and ask them to, to change Austrian Schilling, which they had gotten for their chickens, into forint or-- they had to get into the money changing business in order to go back to Hungary and buy more chickens.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's how they eventually got into the money changing business, through eggs and chickens.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
